  "response_text": "A bright game-like candy selection screen appears on a red fruit-patterned background. At the top left is the Push Pop Gummy Roll logo, and across the top in large yellow-orange letters is the instruction “SELECT SWEET GUMMY CANDY.” Four round Push Pop Gummy Roll dispensers are arranged in a grid: blue, pink, red, and turquoise, each with a yellow frame and a small flavor badge on the front. A white hand-shaped cursor moves between them, and each choice it touches glows with a white outline, as if being selected.\n\nThe scene changes to a colorful cartoon park or game world with green grass, rounded trees, clouds, and distant candy-like buildings. Two children stand in the middle, outlined with a bright white glow. On the left is a light-skinned blonde girl, about preteen age, wearing a coral-red long-sleeved top and dark pants. On the right is a medium-brown-skinned boy of similar age, with tall curly black hair, wearing a black-and-blue color-block sweatshirt and tan pants. They each hold up a Push Pop Gummy Roll dispenser as the word “READY...” appears in large orange letters near the bottom. Fruit graphics, including grapes and a strawberry slice, appear on glowing display panels beside them.\n\nA close view shows hands holding the turquoise Push Pop Gummy Roll dispenser against the grassy game-world background. The dispenser is rounded and palm-sized, with a yellow top and yellow front frame, a blue fruit badge on the side, and a roll of blue gummy candy inside. Along the bottom, bold white words and arrows read “PULL,” “PRESS,” and “PUSH.” A glowing bunch of blue grapes floats to the right over a lit circular platform. The hand lifts or pulls a yellow tab at the top, matching the highlighted “PULL” instruction. The display then emphasizes “PRESS,” and the yellow top is pushed down. Next, the “PUSH” arrow lights up as a blue strip of gummy candy slides out from the side of the dispenser, stretching toward the glowing grape icon.\n\nThe product sits on the grass with the blue gummy strip extended, while the word “PERFECT!” pops up in large orange letters at the bottom. The dispenser rotates slightly, showing the yellow top, turquoise body, and front label as the strip waves out. A hand then holds the dispenser steady with the blue gummy strip protruding. Another hand grips the end of the strip. Large orange words appear at the bottom: first “TEAR,” then “TEAR IT OFF.” The second hand pulls away a bite-sized piece, and small yellow star graphics burst around the dispenser to show the action is completed.\n\nBack in the cartoon park, the two children eat pieces of the gummy strip. The girl holds a turquoise dispenser in one hand and brings a piece to her mouth with the other. The boy holds a yellow-and-turquoise dispenser near his waist and lifts a piece to his open mouth. Both chew and react with pleased expressions. Big orange text reading “YUMMY GUMMY” fills the lower center of the screen, surrounded by glowing yellow stars. The children glance toward each other, then forward, still holding the candy.\n\nThe turquoise Push Pop Gummy Roll dispenser appears alone on a blue background patterned with faint blue fruit silhouettes. The product spins to show its rounded roll shape, yellow top, front label, and the blue gummy strip extending from one side. The word “PERFECT!” remains in bold orange letters along the bottom.\n\nThe final product display appears on a pink background decorated with soft fruit illustrations such as strawberries, watermelon slices, and berry shapes. Multiple Push Pop Gummy Roll packages in bright colors—blue, red, turquoise, and pink—fan out beneath the green-and-yellow Push Pop Gummy Roll logo. Yellow star graphics sparkle around the packages. At the bottom, large white text gives the website: “PUSHPOPGUMMYROLL.COM.”",
